<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>A Rogue Born Of Ice:<br>
The snow was falling lightly, and the wind was still, as Erik McMarrin walked briskly to take over the guard post for his brother Bandl. Erik was the happiest man alive at this moment, his new bride had just told him that she was pregnant. <br>
Azeria is a beautiful, dark skinned, Oasis gypsy that Erik met when his father took him to trade food stuffs with the fine folks in Freeport. It was love at first sight, almost as if she had placed a trance on Erik the minute he walked into her Caravan. It didn't take Erik long to decide Azeria to marry him. They picked her up from the way back from Freeport and took her home to the land of Everfrost.<br>
This particular day was going to live long in Erik's memory. He couldn't be happier. The sun was trying hard to shine through the light clouds and the falling snow. Bandl greeted Erik with a basket full of Roasted Bear meat and Ale as he took over the post. Erik loved it here. All of the young kids who would be learning there trade would come and sit by him to be protected from the occasional bear or leopard that would wander by looking for an easy meal. Some times a Landed Lord or Powerful Wizard would stop by for a chat or to pass on some news from the world abroad. It was about 5 hours into Eriks shift that Bandl came running towards the post. As he stopped Erik could tell that he was not only fatigued but extremely worried about something he left behind. <br>
The next 4 months Erik spent in West Karanas fighting off the Infestation with every able bodied man or woman available. Erik spent every minute thinking about his time away from his beauty and their expecting child. It was hard for him to get away the front line to even write her let alone leave to go see her. Finally the reinforcements from Kunark came in to relieve the battle weary Barbarians and Humans. Erik couldn't be more excited, he was going home. <br>
Getting through Black Burrow was always a challenge. Erik would have to wait until nightfall to sneak his way past the Gnolls that ruled the waterfall. He couldn't help but think how nice it would be to have some Stout to take home to celebrate his childs birth with his family and friends. He decided to take a shortcut and go down a secret entrance in an old tree to see his friend, and Master Brewer, Rufus. The problem is when you meet up with Rufus you have to sample his newest brew. Erik thought, &quot;What the heck, a few more minutes won't make a big difference.&quot;<br>
After a few hours of talking and drinking, laughing and swapping stories, Erik was on his way through the tunnel towards home. Erik was looking forward to seeing his good friend Arlin at the bottom of the ramp into Everfrost. As he got to the bottom of the ramp he saw in his horror an Orc standing over the lifeless body stripping the last bit of armor off Arlins legs. Terror took over. Where did they come from? How did they get through the guard points? Where was Bandl? Terror quickly changed into intense anger at the sight of his fallen friend. His brother was going to have to answer to him. But wait what if they got Bandl too? What if they got my beautiful wife? He started running, faster then he had ever run in his life. &quot;May the Spirit of the Wolves carry me swiftly to the waiting arms of my lovely wife&quot; was his thought as his feet pounded on the hard packed snow. His thoughts flooded with gruesome pictures of family and friends slaughtered brutally at the hands of the Orcs. His head was pounding with panic and the effects of the stout as he tripped and fell down the hill leading out to the Tundra. As he righted himself he could see his house off in the distance. His heart sank. He ran to the top of the hill to get a better view. The small cottage was on fire and he could see the band of Orcs surrounding the house. Frantically looking for any signs of Azeria, Erik screamed at the top of his lungs that it sent a rumble throughout the valley completely startling the Orcs down below. The quickly regained their concentration and set out after Erik. Erik knew his only hope was to run towards the North Tower in hopes that His good pal Tundra Jack would be able to help him. The Orcs had other plans. Erik could hear them gaining ground on him. Erik saw the Tower but no sign of Tundra Jack, he would have to fight.<br>
Erik drew his Mighty Blade and swung with all his might. The power of the blow sent two Orcs to the ground without their grotesque heads. Two more Orcs advanced with spears slashing at Eriks mid-section. Erik parried and brought one to his knees with a swift kick to the groin. A sharp pain took Eriks breath away, he struggled for his breath. When he looked down he saw the end of a spear poking through his breastplate. He fell forward, sword falling from his hands, he caught himself before he completely fell. This was it, he knew he was only moments from death. One more blow from the ruthless Orc and he would be dead. The Orc turned him over breathed heavily into Eriks face and grunted some Orcish. Soon three more Orcs were standing over Erik. Two propped him up on his feet and faced him towards the apparent leader. Then to Eriks horror, the Orc pulled a head from the sack on his waist. It was Azeria. His beloved wife, brutally murdered by these disgusting, ruthless, bloodthirsty Orcs. Rage, sorrow, frustration, and pain took over. Erik lunged forward. In one fell swoop, Erik pulled a dagger from his sleeve and jammed it in the forehead of the Evil before him.<br>
&quot;My wife, my poor lovely wife, these bastards took my wife&quot; Erik said as he felt the life drain from the Orc under him. Then it hit him, &quot;Not just his wife, but his child as well.&quot; The next few moments were a blur. His rage grew with more intensity with each splash of blood each swing of his blade. When he stopped 4 Orcs lay at his feet literally ripped apart. He was weak, his heart pounded, his chest was on fire, Erik knew he would die shortly.<br>
&quot;Why did I leave my wife alone? Why did I stop in BlackBurrow? My poor wife. My child.&quot; all these ideas flashed in Eriks mind as he took his last breath. &quot;May Tunare guide my childs spirit to carry on the memory of its Parents, its Land, its Life&quot;<br>
As Erik slumped over. Tundra Jack leaned down and gently tilted Eriks head into his chest. &quot;Aaaarrrrrggggggg&quot; Jack screamed at the sight of his friends lifeless body. Only the sound of a crying baby brought Tundra Jack back from his deep sadness.<br>
&quot;A baby born of Ice.&quot; Tundra Jack thought to himself. &quot;A child without parents, home, or sureness of life.&quot;<br>
Tundra Jack leaned down and pulled the dagger from the forehead of a slain Orc and wiped it on his tunic. This would be the only thing he could give to the boy in memory of his father.<br>
Kesimar = Wandering <br>
Haakbalas = Dagger<br>
This child would prove his name to be fitting. .<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
